social_posts.post_text: Genuine question for you all:  Have you ever seen something in your life you simply can’t unsee?

I can only imagine the amount of money I would have saved by now if I had a dollar for every time someone tried shaming me for being single.  Lol.  As if being self-partnered, single by choice and happy, is a bad thing?  Meanwhile my fur-son is like, “Ignore the haters dad, you have me!”
This legit happened.  Growing up in the 80s and 90s was just different.  Who remembers? 😩😂

My thoughts: 

What a year it’s been for me.  Honestly, probably one of the most challenging in recent years personally, professionally, and spiritually.  Yeah.. so many challenges including the lost of a few love ones and friends this year while still healing from the lost of others I have had to let transition from the previous year which included my dear fur-daughter Soca, aka @scruffmcfly, who I still very much think of every single day.  Little momma, I can’t thank you enough for those incredible years (close to 15) you gave me.  Daddy still misses you and still baby girl, love you here to the moon.  I mean that!  Speaking of years, hard to believe I turn 44 next month, all while feeling physically like I’m 24 years old.  Yeah.. 22 years of eating plant-based has that incredible perk.  It truly does.  I just wish so many more people can experience it.  I mean it not only helps with one’s health, it also helps this dying planet and more importantly, spares the life of an animal that wants to live and thrive just like us human animals.  Anyhow, happy holidays to anyone reading this spontaneous rant of a caption.  I hope you are very much alive, healthy and well.  I love you all. - Dom ❤️✌🏽
Are y’all holding up ok out there?  #StayStrong #WeAreGoingToGetThroughTheseHolidaysTogether #TeamUs #GodsPlan 🥹😂

Does anyone else have a fur-kid that doesn’t believe you and wants you to take them everywhere with you? And I do mean EVERYWHERE.  From the shower to the grocery store.. to the movies to doing jury duty.  Nowhere is safe! 😩😂. Roc is my real-life shadow I swear.  #SingleDogDadProblems
It’s getting ugly out here in these streets this cold holiday season.  Those exes are getting desperate.  Protect your energy and yourselves my kings and queens.  Stay strong.  #TeamUs ✊🏽🤝🫡😜😂
We truly tried our best. Hahahaha.  Happy new year everyone!  Roc and I truly love you all and wish you the best year ever! ❤️✌🏽🧔🏽‍♂️🐾🐺

New year. New goals. New recipes.  I just made this one this morning after running a few miles and it’s made from juiced carrots!  And it’s gluten-free! Let’s get you started:

1 cup of GF Flour 
1 tsp of cinnamon 
1 cup of juiced carrots 
1 tbsp of egg replacer 
2 tbsp of chia seeds 
1 tbsp oat butter 

1. Mix the dry ingredients in a bowl.

2. Heat waffle maker plates.

3. Cold-press carrots (6-7) with juicer. 

4. Mix the wet and dry ingredients.

5.  Spray hot plates with cold-pressed macadamia oil (preferred).

6. Pour a cup of batter onto hot waffle plates.  Cook for about 2-3 minutes, or set timer for preference.  Add your choice of toppings.  Enjoy! 🌱🐘🐘🐘🐘🐘 #ThisKitchenIsForDancing

#StoryTime Who would have thought, 22 years ago when I got on my knees to pray in my jail cell to God and the universe “I am going to stop eating meat today.. I promise” that my life would shift and change spiritually, physically and ethically, all for the better.  Yeah.. 22 years later, I’m still very much alive, healthy, strong AF and thriving despite my cell mates thinking I was “crazy” and “weird” to give the meat I was served every time at supper to them in exchange for their complex and simple carbs.  You see, during those times, many of us serving time didn’t have much or no money at all on our books to buy additional food so we were stuck with the small quantity and bad quality of food the prison would serve us.  Me being a big guy, I can eat.  And they didn’t serve enough quality complex carbs at times (they served tons of processed carbs), and certainly didn’t serve enough meat to those eating meat so my cell mates were more than happy to exchange food with me despite them thinking I would die from lack of nutrition which is understandable because 22 years ago, the science on plant-based nutrition was behind and society simply didn’t have the data or fancy books, influencers, documentaries and more to show in fact, eating whole plant-based can truly do incredible and I do mean INCREDIBLE things for the health and of the human body.  It also does so much for your mental health and your spiritual energy.  As you can see from the genuine love and bond on in the candid video above.  It’s only so much I can say to you about this lifestyle but this year if you haven’t already, I encourage you to strongly try eating more plant-based.  In fact, try it for this entire month.  I am more than happy to help you get started with our vegan and plant-based program.  Please, give it a shot for the animals, for your health and for this beautiful blue ball planet we all call home.  Click on the link in my bio or go to eatwhatelephantseat.com

Today marks another year around the sun for me and let me tell you, it’s been one hell of an incredible ride full of very high mountains and valleys, extremely deep, dangerous, dark, and low.  But guess what?  You, me and anyone else reading this, is alive and that my friends is something very beautiful and something a human like myself truly appreciates more than you will ever know because so many didn’t wake up today and so many will not wake up tomorrow.  Yeah.. I’m grateful and I hope you are too.  This is 44.  I love you all.  I mean that. - Dom ❤️✌🏽

Sometimes the strongest amongst us become the most vulnerable amongst us.  This includes myself.. 

This is my first post in over 9 months since taking a hiatus from social media.  There were many reasons I decided at that time to take a step back.  Life threw me some really hard and fast curveballs.  I want to talk about 2/4 of them today. 

A little over 2 years ago, shortly after my fur-daughter @scruffmcfly passed away, I decided that I needed to be more “social” and to “get out more” because her death was truly eating me away mentally.  So, I accepted an invite from a fellow dog-dad to play in a adult league play-off game of softball because they were down a few players and needed the help and I figured I needed to break out of that depression mode of losing my fur-daughter and get more active so I said “Sure, why not”. Fast forward to the game, my body and the athlete in me did not disappoint at all.  I excelled and did my thing until it was my time to bat and my eyes, failed me.  While trying to connect on a fast pitch in an effort to hit a home run with all my strength, I sustained not one, but two SLAP tears, in each of my shoulders.  This injury was really bad.  There was a period of time where I couldn’t even cross my arms or put a shirt or coat on myself without severe pain.  I couldn’t even sleep in comfort and living alone, with Roc, it was an even bigger challenge.  I elected not to have surgery for many reasons I’ll discuss at a later time but with some intense rehab and rebuilding of my body through strength training, I finally managed this year to hit a break through and get back up to 90% of my old self for which I’m looking forward to displaying to you all in short-form content going forward. 

Now, to the other curveball I wanted to discuss which is pretty noticeable in this video.  As you can see, the pigment in the finger tips of my hands has lost it color.  I started noticing this change about a year ago.  I honestly thought the marks in some area of my hands and fingers were from breaking up so many dog fights at the dog park.  Continued below in the comments 👇🏽

I truly want to thank everyone for the very kind words of encouragement many of you shared and expressed on my last post of vulnerability.  I’ll have more to say in the very near future regarding vitiligo and some of the insensitive feedback I also received from so many attacking my vegan diet and nutrition, as if my nutrition isn’t incredibly strong AF.  With that being said, I assure you haters my blood work is excellent and I’m not nutrient deficient.  I’m also vegan for life.  In summary, everything isn’t rooted in diet.  Some things are rooted in stresses, trauma, genetics and unknowns.  There is so much ignorance in the world when it comes to science and health and so many people that lack empathy, compassion and the communication tools/skills needed to appropriately and effectively communicate with others.  Aside from the latter, it’s so good to see so many of y’all beautiful faces again.  I missed you sweet potatoes and so did @prettyboyroc. 

Happy National Dog Week from one very proud dog dad! - Dom ❤️✌🏽🐾.
